Interesting!  We would like to announce Part I of the Webinar Series on the Application of New Technologies to Clinical Practice in Neurological Rehabilitation. The Webinar titled  Scientific Evidence and Virtual Reality Applied to Neurological Rehabilitation  will review the latest developments in evidence-based practice in neurological rehabilitation and also analyze the evidence that exists for the application of virtual reality in clinical practice. These will be the main topics covered:  1. Scientific Evidence for Traditional Rehabilitation 2. Scientific Evidence for Virtual Rehabilitation 3. Using Virtual Rehabilitation in Clinical Practice  Registration is free. Please ensure to register early to guarantee your participation. You can click here (http://www.neuroathome.net/2011/09/webinar-series-part-i-scientific.html) to register.  Approximate duration: 60 minutes.

February is the month to raise awareness about Marfan syndrome . Marfanov syndrome belongs to the group of rare diseases . For a rare disease is considered a disease in a country is not a common or affects 5 people per 10 000 population . Marfan syndrome in Slovenia affects 1 patient in 10 000 to 20 000 people. For us  the Marfan syndrome is very rare . Literature on the disease in the Slovenian language hardly . The first simple brochure is available from 2013. In Marfan syndrome symptomatology may occur at a young age but may be noticeable until later during adolescence - adolescence or even later  at the end of adolescence individual. Marfan syndrome is a connective tissue disease   which we have   so to speak throughout the body. Consequently  it can be expected   but not necessarily to Marfan syndrome affects multiple organs or body parts. The most commonly affects the spine   eyes   lungs  aorta - also cardiovascular disease is one for which people worldwide die prematurely   particularly in the case where the syndrome not timely diagnosed and treated . It is important for timely diagnosis and treatment . In the treatment   when the symptomatology extensively involved speciaistov team ( cardiologists   pulmonologists   psychiatrists   orthopedic surgeons   cardiac surgery   neurosurgeons   dentists  ophthalmologists   neurologists ) and   if necessary  other profession . Patients are faced with an unknown disease until the moment of her curiously does not start to look for information on the web or ask their doctors only this   but the more information patients are not exhaustive. It is because the set of all it is important that patients share experiences from several areas and by so doing  help in overcoming daily pain due to a variety of different symptoms. Even through the side of Marfan syndrom Slovenia ( https://www.facebook.com/MarfanSyndromSlovenia) whose purpose is to share information in the field of Marfan development both from home and abroad   unfortunately mostly from abroad. Hoping to improve information for patients   we decided to talk about it in public. In 2013  various media interested helped to raise awareness and thereby ensure that began to talk about this rare disease   which has no year   color - affects both adults and children alike   unfortunately . Join forces and especially in the month of February   the month of raising awareness of Marfan Syndrome frequently visit the page where are you right now and obtain information   because you never know when you re with your knowledge can be friends around you for saving my life   hopefully less often as possible   but if - SUCCESSFUL . Also  in order to prevent the death of children  all patients with the syndrome Marfan I made a page about raising awareness of the syndrome (https://www.facebook.com/MarfanSyndromSlovenia)  which collect information from around the world about this rare disease. FOR ALL FRIEND ALL OWER THE WORLD: A major problem with such rare diseases CLOSENESS patients who  because the nature of the disease do not want to talk about it. Constipation is the result of individuals expectations of misunderstanding  fear of exposure  and other actions that may occur when the patient speaks about his health. My thinking is that it is necessary to talk about the disease  because we can help both themselves and others. Once the disease and its symptomatology so advanced that it leads to an impaired quality of life prevents us from working ability  play sports and other things that are normal in daily life mayority of individuals - so much more can be useful word of awareness about their disease  for us that as well as someone who is completely without any health problem. Of course it can highlight and talk about as unpredictable disease that we are almost a month some patients leads to hospitalization  speciality reviews diagnosis emergency situations  which are the consequences of different symptoms. It also can not deal with every day think that tomorrow may be worse that the outcome of the disease unpredictable and unsettled time. But talk and awareness that can be just one word that can help us overcome even the most difficult moments of everyday coping with the disease  irrespective of its form  it can be very much in favor. Interrelation  conversation  sharing experiences - reciprocity is one of the forms of coping with everyday problems that we both patients and our families etc. (https://www.facebook.com/MarfanSyndromSlovenia)
